          "activation_name": "Signal Flare",
          "effect": "You pull back *Wintershot\u2019s* string and fire an arrow straight upward. The arrow soars to a height of 500 feet, or until it strikes a solid surface like a ceiling. When it reaches its apex, it explodes in a brilliant burst, creating a 100-foot radius area of bright light and dim light in the next 100 feet. In the night sky, this beacon can be seen clearly for miles. The beacon remains lit for up to 1 minute in a color of your choice. Alternately, you can fire a Signal Flare like a normal arrow to attempt to strike a Target\u2014if it hits, the arrow inflicts normal damage and attempts to counteract one darkness effect of your choice that affects the area you hit with a counteract rank of 7th and a counteract modifier of +26.",
          "frequency": "once per day",
